= Heberto Castillo

*Corriente: la nueva izquierda. Cada consejo suyo fortalece a su corriente — y las otras participan menos.*

Engineer, professor, inventor of the tridilosa, survivor of Cerro del Zorrillo and three years of Lecumberri. He is not a member of the Party and says so with a courtesy that stings; he thinks the old left is a beautiful ruin and intends to build something new on the lot next door — with the '68 generation, the nationalist tradition, and Lázaro Cárdenas's ghost as load-bearing elements. But he takes your calls, shares your prisoners' lawyers, and fights beside you more reliably than several people on your Central Committee.

