Heberto does not believe the road runs through the old Party, and he is honest enough to say so to your face — while introducing you to the governors' sons and the Cárdenas people and the nationalist engineers who will, one day not yet named, come looking for a car to crash into the regime. He is laying the bridge years before anyone else sees the river. Walk out onto it a little.
